Here's the full pattern:

**XAML — wrap CollectionView in RefreshView for pull-to-refresh:**

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1"
                           Text="{Binding Name}"
                           VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <Label Text="No items found."
                   HorizontalOptions="Center"
                   VerticalOptions="Center" />
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel (using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm):**

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IItemService _service;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    public ObservableCollection<Item> Items { get; } = new();

    // Pull-to-refresh — reloads from API, then sets IsRefreshing = false
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        var data = await _service.GetItemsAsync();
        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
        {
            Items.Clear();
            foreach (var item in data)
                Items.Add(item);
        });
        IsRefreshing = false;
    }

    // Fires on selection — navigates to detail, then clears selection
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;
        await _nav.GoToAsync($"detail?id={CurrentItem.Id}");
        CurrentItem = null; // reset so user can re-select same item
    }
}
```

**Key bindings explained:**

| Property | Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | Auto-updates UI on add/remove |
| `SelectedItem` | `CurrentItem` (TwoWay) | Tracks which item is tapped |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Triggers navigation on tap |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Fires on pull-to-refresh gesture |
| `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` (TwoWay) | Controls the spinner — set `false` when done |

**Important details:**
- Set `CurrentItem = null` after navigating so the same item can be re-selected.
- Always update `ObservableCollection` on the **UI thread** (`MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`).
- Set `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` to enable compiled bindings.
- Use `ObservableCollection<T>`, never `List<T>` — swapping a `List` forces a full re-render.
